  "text": "Propensity score methods can be used for confounding control in non-experimental research [CITATION_1] . We also carried out a propensity scoring or matching analysis, which is often used to obtain a better estimate of effect size in real-world examples. Propensity score models do not rely on modelling the outcome, but on a model of the treatment given the confounders [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
